    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{5y^{2}x^{2}+7yx+2}{-7yx-4-3y^{2}x^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{5yx+2}{3yx+4}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{5y^{2}x^{2}+7yx+2}{-7yx-4-3y^{2}x^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{\left(5yx+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(yx+1\right)}}{{-3y^{2}x^{2}-7yx-4}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(5yx+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(yx+1\right)}}{{-\left(3y^{2}x^{2}+7yx+4\right)}} \\
                     \amp = \frac{{\left(5yx+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(yx+1\right)}}{{-\left(3yx+4\right)\mathopen{}\left(yx+1\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{5yx+2}{3yx+4}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
